text: Cheryomukha () is a rural locality (a selo) in Krasnoyarsky Selsoviet, Krasnoyarsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 1,157 as of 2010. There are 18 streets. == Geography == It is located 3 km south from Krasny Yar. == References == Category:Rural localities in Krasnoyarsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Cheryomukha
